Defendant in custody.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years, consecutive to the prison sentence presently being served on 17 CF 226, to commence upon defendants discharge date after extended supervision ends.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay court costs;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling/work search/combination;
6) AODA assessment and follow through;
7) Maintain absolute sobriety;
8) Defendant is to use only one doctor to prescribe medications and only one pharmacist to dispense medications unless approved by the agent.
The defendant has credit for 28 days, if revoked.
Minutes.
